WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:25.560 --> 00:30.111
(people chanting)
Al Donnelly! Al Donnelly! Al Donnelly!

00:51.520 --> 00:53.511
(cheering)

01:03.440 --> 01:06.512
And now let's welcome
our hometown hero,

01:06.600 --> 01:10.115
the next governor
of Washington, Al Donnelly!

01:10.200 --> 01:11.997
(cheering)

01:14.400 --> 01:18.791
Attention, Buckley residents.
Voters of all ages, vote for Al Donnelly.

01:18.880 --> 01:23.032
He's the best man for the job.
You can count on Al, that's for sure.

01:23.120 --> 01:27.511
Folks, if you're wondering who to vote
for, Al Donnelly's the man for the job.

01:30.760 --> 01:35.151
I have to go home now, little doggies.
Nothing for you in this truck. No food.

01:36.840 --> 01:38.910
Dogs, I want you to go home.

01:39.160 --> 01:40.752
Get off my bumper!

01:41.320 --> 01:44.357
Come on! Jesus!

01:45.720 --> 01:47.472
Aaagh!

01:47.800 --> 01:49.028
Oh, God!

01:52.640 --> 01:54.631
Oh, my God.

01:58.280 --> 02:02.637
What is with you dogs?! D'you think
this truck is in heat or something?

02:02.720 --> 02:04.711
Get out of here!

02:06.760 --> 02:11.197
If I got the same welcome everywhere
I went that I got here in my home town,

02:11.440 --> 02:13.954
my candidacy would be a lock!

02:14.040 --> 02:15.598
(cheering)

02:19.360 --> 02:21.396
(barks)

02:25.520 --> 02:29.752
With your help, we will make it
all the way to the Capitol!

02:32.200 --> 02:37.149
(chanting) Al Donnelly! Al Donnelly!
Al Donnelly! Al Donnelly!

02:37.240 --> 02:40.232
(amplified barking and growling)

02:43.720 --> 02:46.917
- Did you do this?
- No, no, no... Did you?

02:47.200 --> 02:49.031
(growling)

03:03.400 --> 03:04.913
Oh, my God.

03:14.120 --> 03:15.758
Oh, my God.

03:15.880 --> 03:17.836
- (woman screams)
- Mother...

03:35.880 --> 03:37.757
Oh, there is a God.

03:39.440 --> 03:41.635
Tell me that is not your brother.

03:42.520 --> 03:45.239
What the hell is a marquee doin' here?
It's crazy!

03:49.800 --> 03:53.110
Al, I'm so sorry.
Man, I don't know what happened.

03:53.200 --> 03:55.873
Mike, forget it.
Did you think it was a drive-in movie?

03:55.960 --> 03:56.949
(both laugh)

03:57.720 --> 03:59.199
(blasts horn)

03:59.520 --> 04:04.548
I could get time off from the rec centre.
They said I could, to help you campaign.

04:04.640 --> 04:08.713
So I was thinking maybe I could go
on the road with you and help out, or...

04:08.800 --> 04:13.715
Mike, I know you're behind me 100%,
but I need some different help from you.

04:14.120 --> 04:16.714
Oh, man, whatever you want.
You know that.

04:16.800 --> 04:19.189
- Fighting Donnellys stick together!
- Right!

04:19.279 --> 04:23.159
Listen, I got a lot of good people
in my corner. They want what we want.

04:23.240 --> 04:27.199
And we're gonna get there.
It's just gonna take some finesse.

04:27.600 --> 04:30.273
I'll do anything.
Just name it and I'll get started.

04:30.360 --> 04:34.194
There's a lot to be done right here,
like phone canvassing, stuff like that.

04:34.280 --> 04:37.477
So stay put and I'll get you
the details. All right?

04:37.560 --> 04:40.233
- We gonna do it, little brother?
- Yeah!

04:42.000 --> 04:45.595
- Come on. Let's go.
- All the way, Governor.

04:53.920 --> 04:56.195
Dock Workers' Union.

04:56.280 --> 04:59.716
Let me make myself clear.
My brother is a priority.

04:59.800 --> 05:02.394
Let's just find someone
in the organisation.

05:02.480 --> 05:07.031
Just as long as he or she is reliable
and helps Mike make a contribution.

05:07.120 --> 05:11.955
So just find someone and
give them the assignment... now.

05:12.040 --> 05:14.952
(man) Excuse me <i>, </i> Mr "About to be
Governor Elect" Donnelly.

05:15.040 --> 05:20.398
This assignment you describe <i>, </i>
if someone volunteered and did it well <i>, </i>

05:20.480 --> 05:23.995
would he or she earn a staff position
in your new administration?

05:24.080 --> 05:28.392
- Steve, not now.
- Hey. Uh, yes.

05:28.480 --> 05:30.994
He or she most certainly would.

05:34.720 --> 05:36.711
Then I am your man.

05:38.040 --> 05:40.395
(ringing tone)

05:40.480 --> 05:44.075
Hi. This is Mike Donnelly. I work
over here at the recreational centre.

05:44.160 --> 05:46.720
To be honest,
I pretty much run the place!

05:46.800 --> 05:49.678
Is this, uh, Pat Giles?

05:49.760 --> 05:50.954
Good. Good.

05:51.040 --> 05:56.239
Hey, I hope everything's going great in
your fine town of, uh, Avery... Atwood.

05:57.240 --> 06:01.597
The reason I'm calling is I wanted to tell
you about the candidacy of Al Donnelly.

06:01.680 --> 06:06.435
Al Donnelly's a guy with a dream. His
dream is to be governor of Washington.

06:06.520 --> 06:12.629
Hell, every guy's got his dream, am I
right? I had a doozie myself last night!

06:12.720 --> 06:17.475
Get this: a cornfed harvest mouse,
a hooker, a nun, a Flemish woman,

06:17.720 --> 06:21.349
whips, chains, whistles,
yo-yos, a circus midget,

06:21.440 --> 06:25.399
my grandmother riding by on a bicycle
giving me the finger, and a duck.

06:25.480 --> 06:28.836
Now, I don't know... Are you crying?

06:29.160 --> 06:31.628
Oh, my Lord. I am sorry.

06:31.720 --> 06:34.996
Honey, please don't. Could you
get your daddy on the phone?

06:35.080 --> 06:37.833
- No, don't hang up, please. I...
- (hangs up)

06:41.640 --> 06:43.517
Whoa.

06:43.600 --> 06:48.196
All right, I want a 32 belly option
on two, on two. Ready? Break!

06:52.400 --> 06:54.356
Hut one. Hut two.

06:54.440 --> 06:56.431
Let's do it!

07:05.360 --> 07:06.952
Oh, hey, little girls.

07:08.720 --> 07:10.597
Yeah!

07:10.680 --> 07:14.150
(cheering and whooping)

07:14.240 --> 07:16.549
This sucks! These teams aren't fair.

07:16.640 --> 07:20.838
What's wrong, Sullivan? You mad cos
you found out the new kid got an arm?

07:20.920 --> 07:24.515
- Suckers, take the walk.
- Screw this. I quit.

07:25.480 --> 07:28.870
Fine then. Here's to the winners. Yeah!

07:28.960 --> 07:32.999
Kemp, fake head butt. DeSalvo, fake
head butt. New kid, fake head butt.

07:33.160 --> 07:35.355
Ow! You broke my nose!

07:35.560 --> 07:36.754
Oh!

07:36.840 --> 07:41.709
- There's so much blood.
- I swear I did not mean to do it! Please!

07:41.800 --> 07:43.995
- Ketchup packet.
- (laughter)

07:44.080 --> 07:46.992
Come on, guys. This is weird.
Let's go play some kickball.

07:47.080 --> 07:49.071
Yeah, come on.

07:51.240 --> 07:53.356
Forget those guys.

07:53.440 --> 07:55.908
- What's your name?
- Scott Colleary.

07:56.000 --> 07:57.592
Colleary.

07:57.680 --> 08:00.478
- You got a hell of an arm, Colleary.
- Thanks.

08:00.560 --> 08:01.959
Yeah.

08:02.040 --> 08:05.077
- Don't worry about those guys.
- They don't like me too much.

08:05.160 --> 08:08.357
- Is your mom picking you up?
- My mom and dad got a divorce.

08:08.440 --> 08:10.874
I have to live with my grandma now.

08:15.960 --> 08:20.795
Oh, come on. Label your streets
like the rest of the country.

08:24.720 --> 08:27.154
Oh! Oh! Buddy, are you OK?

08:27.680 --> 08:31.434
I'm not that far from dragging you
out of the car and beating you into dust.

08:31.520 --> 08:35.308
You should work up to that.
Kind of leaves you nowhere to go.

08:36.360 --> 08:39.830
I can go to your mama's
and start a small fire in her panties.

08:39.919 --> 08:42.150
Now, are you ready
to get out of the car?

08:42.840 --> 08:47.231
No, sir. You know what?
That was my fault and I'm really sorry.

08:47.320 --> 08:49.959
Here, I got something for you.
It's a souvenir.

08:50.040 --> 08:52.395
Oh, here it is! Yeah!

08:52.480 --> 08:54.118
Goodbye!

08:59.920 --> 09:01.751
- Oh, shit.
- (honking)

09:01.840 --> 09:03.637
I don't believe this.

09:03.720 --> 09:05.915
Damn it. I gotta ditch this guy.

09:17.720 --> 09:19.517
Hey!

09:21.320 --> 09:24.278
- That's my grandma. Mrs Oneacre.
- Hi, ma'am.

09:25.280 --> 09:27.555
Bet you made
some nice friends today, huh?

09:28.280 --> 09:30.271
(Scott) See ya.

09:33.080 --> 09:36.675
Scott. God gave you
a hell of a throwin' arm,

09:36.760 --> 09:38.910
and I'll be damned
if I'll let that go to waste.

09:39.000 --> 09:42.515
I want you on the field every day
working on your game. How's that?

09:42.600 --> 09:44.909
- Sure.
- Nice to meet you, ma'am.

10:02.440 --> 10:04.237
- Hey, Mikey.
- Hey, Robbie.

10:04.320 --> 10:07.835
I spoke to Anderson at the theatre.
He wants me to lock you up.

10:08.840 --> 10:10.990
I bet your brother's pissed, huh?

10:11.080 --> 10:13.719
No, he was pretty cool, as usual.

10:13.800 --> 10:15.597
I wanna show you something.

10:15.680 --> 10:18.877
In fact, I'm gonna be working
with one of his top guys.

10:22.040 --> 10:24.873
Whoa! Nitrous oxide boosters!

10:24.960 --> 10:28.236
- This thing must haul major ass.
- You could say that.

10:35.360 --> 10:37.157
Oh, great.

10:37.240 --> 10:39.037
Damn it.

10:40.720 --> 10:43.632
- Get out of my way, buddy.
- Lady, I got somethin' for ya.

10:43.720 --> 10:45.870
- A souvenir for you here.
- Yes?

10:47.880 --> 10:49.711
Never mind. Forget it.

10:49.800 --> 10:53.429
What are you doing?
Playing pocket pool there, son?

10:53.520 --> 10:56.751
- Excuse me.
- You got a little chubby goin' there.

10:57.320 --> 10:59.311
Dream on, you little fart.

11:14.160 --> 11:16.594
Please don't be Mike Donnelly.

11:16.680 --> 11:17.351
Hi.

11:17.440 --> 11:21.115
Hey. I'm Steve Dodds,
one of your brother's advisors.

11:21.200 --> 11:24.988
- His top advisor, actually.
- Wow. It's great to meet you.

11:25.080 --> 11:28.231
Nice to, um, see you.

11:28.320 --> 11:31.630
Al, your brother, told me
to drop everything, come down here,

11:31.720 --> 11:34.553
get you organised for the final push,
for the election.

11:34.640 --> 11:38.428
Well, let's get to it. Team Donnelly
gonna kick a little Tracy butt.

11:38.520 --> 11:40.238
Oh! Aaargh!

11:40.640 --> 11:45.634
What I thought is, we'd start with the
supermarket, canvass that area first.

11:45.720 --> 11:48.314
- I...
- No, trust me on this. It's a good idea.

11:49.160 --> 11:52.038
- But...
- Listen, I'm running this show.

11:52.120 --> 11:54.076
- I know what I'm doing.
- (moans)

11:54.920 --> 11:59.471
- D'you have to go to the bathroom?
- Please... pop... the hood.

12:00.000 --> 12:02.673
- Please!
- Oh, your thumbs. The hood. OK.

12:02.760 --> 12:06.355
- What latch? Where d'you want me to...
- Just pop the hood!

12:06.520 --> 12:08.511
Please!

12:08.600 --> 12:10.591
Popping the hood.

12:14.000 --> 12:16.275
(wails)

12:16.600 --> 12:19.831
Good afternoon. We'd like you
to vote Al Donnelly for governor.

12:19.920 --> 12:21.911
Yeah, thanks.

12:22.600 --> 12:24.591
- Hi, ma'am.
- (gasps)

12:25.560 --> 12:27.835
Vote for Donnelly.

12:27.920 --> 12:29.717
Sorry.

12:29.800 --> 12:32.439
I think it's better
if we bring the energy down a tad.

12:32.520 --> 12:34.954
Are you kidding me?
These are potential voters.

12:35.040 --> 12:38.077
It's showmanship.
You gotta go out and get 'em.

12:38.160 --> 12:40.151
Watch and learn.

12:40.840 --> 12:43.479
- Hi, folks. Vote for Donnelly!
- Good God, man.

12:43.560 --> 12:46.154
- Let me get that for you.
- Look, I drove down here.

12:46.240 --> 12:50.438
- I can put the groceries in the trunk.
- Help from the Donnelly campaign.

12:50.520 --> 12:52.238
- Back off, buster.
- Oh!

12:53.640 --> 12:56.108
- Come on, Mother.
- Let me help you, sir.

12:56.200 --> 12:59.317
- Get in the car, dear.
- All right, Mother.

13:06.840 --> 13:09.718
Folks, I'm having a little trouble here.

13:09.800 --> 13:12.598
Help! Help, please!

13:12.800 --> 13:15.598
He must be all hopped up
on crack cocaine.

13:15.680 --> 13:18.069
Floor it, Harold!

13:20.520 --> 13:22.590
I can't! I can't!

13:22.680 --> 13:24.910
Argh! Help!

13:27.280 --> 13:30.989
- Good. I think I've lost him.
- Stop! Please!

13:31.080 --> 13:33.275
Aargh!

13:33.360 --> 13:34.839
Aargh!

13:47.560 --> 13:49.152
OK.

13:49.240 --> 13:51.231
- Good first day.
- Yeah.

13:56.280 --> 14:00.193
Washington State.
Isn't it a great place to raise a family?

14:00.280 --> 14:03.989
That's because for the last eight years
I've worked hard as your governor

14:04.080 --> 14:08.596
to make sure our state
is clean, safe and fiscally sound.

14:08.680 --> 14:12.116
If re-elected to a third term,
I'll do my best as your governor

14:12.200 --> 14:16.079
to make sure that all the hopes and
dreams of Washingtonians come true.

14:16.160 --> 14:19.755
- (man) And cut.
- I need a break. I'll be right back.

14:20.880 --> 14:22.871
Did you get the latest polls?

14:23.800 --> 14:28.032
Donnelly's brother took a campaign van
on a rampage. He can't get a break!

14:28.120 --> 14:32.398
- But they gained another two points.
- We're OK. A lot can be done in a week.

14:32.480 --> 14:36.075
If we don't do something soon,
he'll be living here.

14:37.360 --> 14:39.032
Who left this crap in here?

14:46.280 --> 14:48.510
Promise me you'll stay in the car.

14:48.600 --> 14:50.670
I promise.

14:55.240 --> 14:57.231
(excited chatter)

15:01.400 --> 15:05.951
Whoa! What have we got here?
A tall cool one!

15:06.040 --> 15:07.712
Yeah!

15:08.040 --> 15:09.712
Go for it.

15:09.800 --> 15:11.995
- I wanna get wrecked!
- (all laugh)

15:17.240 --> 15:19.470
Oh, yeah, man!

15:23.720 --> 15:28.748
# Smokin', snortin', shootin',
suckin', tokin', poppin', droppin'

15:29.120 --> 15:31.315
Let's do a little dance.

15:33.720 --> 15:35.358
A party with you!

15:36.800 --> 15:39.394
- The kid's a star.
- No, he's a gold mine.

15:41.600 --> 15:44.194
- (Mike) Ah. Horseshit!
- (glass smashes)

15:45.440 --> 15:48.432
- Front page.
- Jesus, Mike!

15:48.520 --> 15:52.354
But it turns out he was giving these
kids a speech about saying no to drugs.

15:52.440 --> 15:57.355
- Can the paper print a retraction?
- They'll run it on page 36 in two weeks!

15:58.720 --> 16:01.280
Al, you can take this election.

16:01.360 --> 16:06.718
But your brother is creating his own
media feeding frenzy-all negative.

16:06.800 --> 16:09.394
We have got to put a lid on him.

16:09.480 --> 16:12.392
You're right.
But he doesn't deserve to be exiled.

16:12.480 --> 16:17.031
You just tell Steve to watch him like a
hawk and to keep the reporters at bay.

16:17.120 --> 16:18.712
(cheering)

16:19.800 --> 16:23.429
Welcome, Washington
Teachers' Association!

16:23.600 --> 16:25.397
Welcome!

16:26.640 --> 16:31.111
Washington has the most
beautiful forests in America.

16:31.200 --> 16:35.751
And I am proud to be
an honorary Clark County lumberjack.

16:43.120 --> 16:45.839
- The tree's not falling.
- Yeah, I know.

16:47.760 --> 16:51.116
Don't let anyone ever tell you
your job is easy.

16:57.320 --> 16:59.276
Oh, my God!

17:03.760 --> 17:04.714
You make the call. The rest
is for damage control. You stay put.

17:07.119 --> 17:09.554
Thank you, gentlemen.
Excuse us just a moment.

17:11.079 --> 17:14.117
What happened? It should've
gone down on the first whack.

17:14.200 --> 17:16.031
You covered really well.

17:16.119 --> 17:18.953
You're lucky a kid didn't get
his head cracked wide open.

17:19.040 --> 17:20.029
Yes, ma'am.

17:20.119 --> 17:23.795
- Did you get the numbers in?
- Oh. Hot off the wire.

17:25.560 --> 17:29.519
- Donnelly's levelled off.
- Mm-hm. We're dead even. Look at this.

17:31.040 --> 17:32.439
Front page.

17:32.520 --> 17:35.512
"Donnelly's brother is like
Roger Clinton, Billy Carter

17:35.600 --> 17:38.592
and Ronald Reagan's
entire family rolled into one."

17:39.200 --> 17:43.671
Let's move this out of the land of
mere embarrassment into the realm...

17:43.760 --> 17:45.671
of serious effect.

17:45.760 --> 17:48.718
- Ready to play the game?
- I've got some pretty nasty ideas.

17:48.800 --> 17:51.439
Good. Act on them.

17:52.280 --> 17:55.158
- I've been fired.
- What? Why?

17:56.240 --> 17:59.710
He said the rec centre's state-funded.

17:59.800 --> 18:02.792
He can't afford to be associated
with any kind of a scandal,

18:02.880 --> 18:06.077
especially one
involving kids and drugs.

18:06.160 --> 18:11.553
He said he stood up for me, but word
came from the top for me to get out.

18:12.920 --> 18:15.434
It's crazy, man.
I don't know what to say.

18:15.520 --> 18:18.717
I love this job. I've been here
since the place opened.

18:20.480 --> 18:22.471
And then they just...

18:25.240 --> 18:30.189
Dude, can I get a couple of minutes
just to clear some of the gear out?

18:30.600 --> 18:32.591
Yeah, sure.

18:32.680 --> 18:34.989
Hey, I'm sorry, man. Take your time.

19:38.920 --> 19:40.911
(chatter)

19:48.800 --> 19:51.109
Hey, fellas. How's it goin'?
Can I help you?

19:53.200 --> 19:58.035
Hey, Mike. How's things? Kind of
pissed off about losing your job, huh?

19:58.680 --> 20:03.435
- All right, pal. What's goin' on here?
- You shouldn't play with matches.

20:04.560 --> 20:06.949
Hey! What the hell are you doing?

20:10.640 --> 20:12.437
God!

20:17.320 --> 20:18.912
(Mike shouts)

20:21.080 --> 20:23.071
Shit!

20:23.960 --> 20:25.632
Oh, my God!

20:29.040 --> 20:32.316
- Why in the hell?! No!
- (siren)

20:32.400 --> 20:34.994
Mike, how the hell did this happen?

20:43.720 --> 20:47.429
- Robbie, you know I didn't do this.
- Jesus, Mike. Give me some credit.

20:47.520 --> 20:50.318
- Did you see who did it?
- Two guys. I don't know them.

20:50.400 --> 20:53.437
They didn't count on me getting here
first. Look, get out of here.

20:53.520 --> 20:57.991
When the troopers arrive, I'll tell them
I didn't find anybody here. All right?

20:58.080 --> 21:00.389
- Go ahead. Take off.
- Thanks, Robbie.

21:01.720 --> 21:03.870
- I owe you one, man.
- Call me later.

21:03.960 --> 21:05.439
(distant sirens)

21:05.520 --> 21:09.718
Base, this is Mieghem. I'm at the rec
centre. Send fire units and a backup.

21:09.800 --> 21:11.791
I'm the only one down here.

21:13.520 --> 21:17.911
- Well, did he do it or not?
- Kovary, I lean toward the negative.

21:18.000 --> 21:20.230
- I know what you're saying.
- Shh.

21:20.320 --> 21:23.118
Give me the phone.
Steve, it's Al. What is going on?

21:23.200 --> 21:27.398
- Hey, Al. Well, in my opinion...
- I wanna talk to my brother.

21:27.600 --> 21:31.149
Al, I know how this must look,
but I had nothing to do with that fire.

21:31.480 --> 21:34.836
I loved that place. It was my life.
You gotta believe me!

21:34.920 --> 21:38.959
I believe you. You were set up. And
we're gonna get to the bottom of this.

21:39.040 --> 21:41.429
We have a game plan. Don't we, Roger?

21:42.720 --> 21:46.110
- Tell me what to do and I'll do it.
- Roger and Steve'll work it out.

21:46.200 --> 21:49.829
Mike, don't worry.
Everything is gonna be OK, I promise.

21:49.920 --> 21:51.911
Thanks, Al. Thanks.

21:53.320 --> 21:56.232
- Steve here.
- Meet me downstairs in the lobby.

21:58.560 --> 22:02.189
Dodds, listen to me very carefully.

22:02.280 --> 22:05.829
We have got to keep this... this bozo

22:05.920 --> 22:08.514
under wraps until the election is over.

22:08.600 --> 22:11.797
Now, I want you to do
exactly as I tell you.

22:11.880 --> 22:14.952
- Yeah. OK. Keep talking.
- I know a place way outside town.

22:42.920 --> 22:45.514
All right! Bunk beds!

22:45.880 --> 22:48.678
- I got dibs on top.
- OK.

22:49.680 --> 22:51.796
(Steve) First class, right?

22:51.880 --> 22:54.474
- What's that black thing?
- What?

22:58.960 --> 23:01.155
I don't know.

23:01.600 --> 23:05.036
- Touch it.
- What? You touch it.

23:05.120 --> 23:07.156
- You afraid?
- No, I'll touch it.

23:07.840 --> 23:11.310
- You totally didn't touch it.
- Well, then you touch it.

23:11.400 --> 23:13.994
- I will if you will.
- All right.

23:15.320 --> 23:17.629
- (bat screeches)
- (both) Whoa! Man!

23:19.120 --> 23:21.873
- What is that?
- It's Ozzy Osbourne. Whoa!

23:22.120 --> 23:24.111
Oh, my God.

23:25.160 --> 23:26.354
Whoa.

23:26.440 --> 23:29.352
- I think it's gone.
- I hate those damn things.

23:29.440 --> 23:32.273
- (screeching)
- Oh, man!

23:32.360 --> 23:33.759
Agh! Agh!

23:33.840 --> 23:37.389
It bit me! I'm gonna get rabies!

23:37.480 --> 23:39.471
I'm stuck. I'm stuck.

23:45.000 --> 23:46.991
Come on! Oh!

23:50.600 --> 23:52.670
I got an idea. OK?

23:52.760 --> 23:56.435
I'll open the fridge, you hit the lights.
Bats are attracted to light.

23:56.520 --> 23:59.796
He'll fly in the fridge,
I close the door, end of story.

24:00.080 --> 24:03.789
- That's moths, you dumb-ass, not bats.
- Oh, yeah, moths.

24:04.560 --> 24:06.357
Eegh!

24:07.160 --> 24:08.752
Watch this.

24:20.200 --> 24:22.589
That's it. Corner it.

24:27.000 --> 24:30.231
- I think I got it.
- No way.

24:30.320 --> 24:32.914
- I think it's in there.
- Well, then look.

24:34.240 --> 24:36.231
You look.

24:36.320 --> 24:39.517
All right. We'll both look together.

24:39.600 --> 24:42.433
One, two...

24:42.520 --> 24:44.511
- Three!
- Agh!

24:45.240 --> 24:46.958
You idiot!

24:47.040 --> 24:50.635
You can't catch a bat with a pot, moron.

24:50.720 --> 24:53.518
You take a mop and a broom... Oh!

24:53.800 --> 24:57.475
- Oh, God! Oh! Oh! Oh, God!
- (screeches)

25:04.680 --> 25:06.955
Get this thing off me!
What the hell are you...

25:07.040 --> 25:08.678
Ow! Ow!

25:08.760 --> 25:12.548
Why are you hitting me? Ow!
It's gnawing at my skull.

25:12.640 --> 25:14.153
For God's sakes!

25:14.240 --> 25:16.470
Ow! Ow!

25:16.560 --> 25:20.553
- Die! Die!
- Please! You're aggravating it!

25:22.840 --> 25:25.638
Why are you kicking me? Ow!

25:25.720 --> 25:28.109
- I can't see a damn thing!
- Die!

25:28.200 --> 25:30.634
- Oh, Jesus!
- I think I nailed it!

25:30.720 --> 25:33.473
- (screeching)
- I don't believe it. He's still alive.

25:33.560 --> 25:36.393
Can we please try my idea?

25:36.480 --> 25:41.315
Come on! Hold the thing tight
so it gets in there.

25:41.400 --> 25:44.392
- I'm trying.
- Well, try harder. Stay over there.

25:44.480 --> 25:48.951
Moron! OK, it's flying in now. It's flying
in now. It's flying right in the middle.

25:49.040 --> 25:52.271
- It touched my hand.
- If this doesn't work I'll sleep in the car.

25:52.360 --> 25:54.954
Stay there. OK. OK.
It's right in the middle.

25:55.040 --> 25:57.838
OK, we got it, we got it, we got it...

25:57.920 --> 25:59.911
It's outta there.

26:04.120 --> 26:06.270
Good night, Steve.

26:06.360 --> 26:08.157
Good night, Mike.

26:09.200 --> 26:12.749
The police officer who arrived
before our guys was a friend of Mike's.

26:12.840 --> 26:17.868
He let him go and didn't report seeing
him, so Mike wasn't linked to the fire.

26:20.120 --> 26:25.353
Neuschwander, you finished stirring, or
is this a fucking science experiment?!

26:25.440 --> 26:30.309
I realise you must stick close together
cos you share a common backbone,

26:30.400 --> 26:32.994
but I wanna see some movement!

26:34.360 --> 26:35.839
Now!

26:37.800 --> 26:41.509
This is great. There's 1,502
registered voters in Garfield County.

26:41.600 --> 26:43.397
Go get 'em, Al.

26:43.480 --> 26:46.995
Hey, pretty good day. No screwups.
Keep up the good work.

26:48.680 --> 26:50.955
I'm gonna go take a squeege.

26:58.480 --> 27:00.994
Oh, God!

27:01.080 --> 27:02.274
(echoes)

27:09.040 --> 27:11.031
(insufficient signal tone)

27:19.520 --> 27:21.954
- (insufficient signal tone)
- (sighs)

27:27.240 --> 27:29.117
Eegh! Oh!

27:42.880 --> 27:44.871
(insufficient signal tone)

27:46.320 --> 27:48.311
What is wrong?

27:49.640 --> 27:53.269
Oh, something tells me
I want this car to just keep driving.

27:56.080 --> 27:57.991
Hey, gang.

28:00.320 --> 28:02.959
Is there an Opie convention in town?

28:05.240 --> 28:07.879
- I'm kidding.
- You're not from around here, huh?

28:08.600 --> 28:12.912
- You know what, I am. Born and raised.
- Nope. Can't be true.

28:19.640 --> 28:21.596
Fire!

28:35.240 --> 28:38.073
Thanks for not shoving
the nozzle up my ass first!

28:38.160 --> 28:41.118
(tyres screech <i>, </i> kids yell)

28:46.560 --> 28:49.154
- Vote for Donnelly.
- (echoes)

28:51.840 --> 28:53.831
Every vote counts.

28:54.680 --> 28:56.671
Argh!

29:09.120 --> 29:10.712
Oh.

29:17.160 --> 29:18.957
Aaargh!

29:19.280 --> 29:21.271
No, no, no, no!

29:27.160 --> 29:29.037
Oh. Oh.

29:29.120 --> 29:32.351
Oh, thank you, little roots.

29:32.640 --> 29:34.631
Please stay strong.

29:57.240 --> 30:00.630
What in the hell was that all about?

30:14.400 --> 30:17.915
You freaks better be careful,
cos next time I don't go down so easy.

30:18.120 --> 30:21.271
Next time I'll be, like, "You wanna
spray me? How about this?"

30:21.360 --> 30:23.032
Arm grab! Aie!

30:23.120 --> 30:25.350
Snap kick! Side kick!

30:26.160 --> 30:29.948
Rabbit punch!
Rabbit punch, into pile-driver!

30:30.040 --> 30:32.429
That's right, my friend. It's a pile-driver.

30:32.520 --> 30:35.034
Oh, who else wants some? You?

30:35.120 --> 30:38.112
Sleeper hold. Oh, yeah. Oh, yeah.

30:43.240 --> 30:45.231
Hey, that's my car.

30:46.640 --> 30:48.631
It's that same asshole. Whoo!

30:51.800 --> 30:53.028
- (phone rings)
- Oh.

30:54.520 --> 30:57.034
(imitates a "ringing" bird call)

30:57.120 --> 30:59.111
What the hell was that?

31:06.920 --> 31:10.515
Whoa, what happened to you?
D'you fall in some mud or something?

31:10.600 --> 31:13.239
Yeah, I did. And I'm gonna be rich,

31:13.320 --> 31:16.710
because I'm the only person on earth
who knows where to find white mud.

31:17.560 --> 31:22.270
I didn't say "mud". I said "crud".
D'you fall into some crud or something?

31:22.360 --> 31:26.990
- Get some water to wipe off that crud.
- I'm not a kid that'd believe that.

31:27.080 --> 31:29.799
- Shut up, Steve. Where'd you go?
- To make a call.

31:29.880 --> 31:35.238
Remember I told you a guy stole my
car? He's a mile away. He's driving it.

31:35.320 --> 31:40.394
- Well, let's go get it back.
- Uh-uh. This guy is unstable, at best.

31:40.480 --> 31:43.711
You can't keep running away
from things. You gotta be tough.

31:43.800 --> 31:46.439
Argh! Argh!

31:46.520 --> 31:49.592
Snakes! Oh, no!

31:49.680 --> 31:51.671
One looked at me!

31:53.200 --> 31:56.988
Check your underpants!
I hate those things!

31:59.080 --> 32:02.356
- This gets worse every second.
- I hate snakes!

32:06.360 --> 32:08.794
(both scream)

32:10.720 --> 32:12.995
Whoa. Check it out.

32:13.080 --> 32:17.119
- Jump in. Wash that crap off.
- There's probably piranha in there.

32:17.200 --> 32:20.829
- This place is a nightmare.
- Get tough, nancy boy. Jump in.

32:23.520 --> 32:25.511
I don't see you goin' in.

32:27.800 --> 32:29.791
Ugh.

32:32.360 --> 32:34.316
Where'd you go?

32:34.400 --> 32:37.073
Hello, Washington!

32:37.160 --> 32:39.469
Yeah!

32:39.560 --> 32:42.552
Aaaargh!

33:13.840 --> 33:16.354
De-de-de, do-do-do! (laughs)

33:16.440 --> 33:19.159
This is great. I've never won
three games in a row.

33:19.240 --> 33:21.231
I hardly ever play checkers.

33:21.320 --> 33:26.872
Yeah, yeah. Well, you know,
it's kinda easy to win when you, um...

33:26.960 --> 33:28.951
never move your back row!

33:29.480 --> 33:31.152
Ever!

33:31.240 --> 33:33.595
God! Come on!

33:33.960 --> 33:37.509
OK, well, where would you
want me to move this one?

33:39.800 --> 33:41.756
There.

33:44.240 --> 33:46.231
King me!

33:48.160 --> 33:51.516
OK. Move this one here.
It's safe, I swear. It's safe.

33:51.600 --> 33:52.874
(laughs)

33:52.960 --> 33:55.394
That wasn't safe at all.
What an idiot.

33:56.840 --> 33:59.434
- Oh, this is fun.
- Yeah, yeah, it was.

33:59.760 --> 34:01.751
(bird cries)

34:12.080 --> 34:13.149
What's goin' on?

34:15.520 --> 34:17.511
That's not normal.

34:20.000 --> 34:22.195
(both scream)

34:43.960 --> 34:46.349
How the hell did that happen?

34:49.159 --> 34:50.559
Ow.

34:50.639 --> 34:52.596
Oh.

34:52.679 --> 34:54.670
Oh, man!

35:01.960 --> 35:05.316
- This place is trashed.
- Check this out.

35:05.400 --> 35:08.517
This whole fridge is held up here
just by this plug.

35:09.680 --> 35:11.318
(Mike screams)

35:14.200 --> 35:16.509
(groans)

35:22.120 --> 35:24.315
You OK?

35:26.200 --> 35:31.479
I'm just dandy! I got a bowl of
chocolate pudding in my underpants!

35:32.320 --> 35:35.118
We didn't have
any pudding in there, buddy.

35:38.480 --> 35:42.234
(Mike) This sucks. I can't believe
I forgot to call Scott Colleary.

35:42.320 --> 35:44.754
Good luck getting out.
It's never gonna work.

35:44.840 --> 35:47.593
Yes, it will.
All you need to do is get a signal.

35:47.680 --> 35:49.671
(insufficient signal tone)

36:00.200 --> 36:01.792
- (ringing tone)
- Hello?

36:01.880 --> 36:03.518
- Hello?
- Hello?

36:03.600 --> 36:04.794
- Hello?
- Hello?

36:04.880 --> 36:07.474
- Mrs Oneacre? Hello? Mrs Oneacre?
- Yes.

36:09.920 --> 36:12.832
Hello? Are you there?

36:12.920 --> 36:15.514
Hello. This is Mrs Oneacre.
Are you there?

36:16.920 --> 36:19.878
Mrs Oneacre, it's Mike Donnelly.
Is Scott there?

36:19.960 --> 36:21.916
No.

36:22.000 --> 36:24.514
Oh, jeez. I had to leave town.

36:24.600 --> 36:27.797
Could you tell him I'm sorry
and I'll make it up to him?

36:27.880 --> 36:30.394
- Yes.
- (moans) Don't forget to tell him that.

36:30.480 --> 36:32.471
- Bye.
- Hello?

36:54.800 --> 36:56.791
Good night, Steve.

36:57.960 --> 36:59.951
Good night, Mike.

37:03.360 --> 37:05.555
(wind howling)

37:05.680 --> 37:07.477
(creaking)

37:10.360 --> 37:12.351
(snores)

37:18.880 --> 37:20.677
Ow!

37:21.680 --> 37:22.954
Oh, man.

37:25.320 --> 37:27.470
- Oh, God.
- I don't like this, Mike.

37:28.760 --> 37:30.034
Mike?

37:32.040 --> 37:34.508
Ooh! Ooh! Ooh!

37:35.280 --> 37:37.271
(Steve) Whoa!

37:42.000 --> 37:43.991
This sucks!

37:45.080 --> 37:47.878
- Good night, Steve.
- Good night, Mike.

37:49.480 --> 37:51.471
(thunder rumbling)

38:12.120 --> 38:15.351
Hey, Mike. "I got dibs on top bunk"!

38:15.440 --> 38:17.032
Shut up.

38:17.120 --> 38:19.315
(laughs derisively)

38:19.400 --> 38:21.630
- Oh, I love it.
- Why don't you shut up?

38:21.720 --> 38:23.517
"Hello, Washington!"

38:23.960 --> 38:26.758
- How's the weather up there, buddy?
- Shut up!

38:26.840 --> 38:29.673
(Steve carries on laughing)

38:29.760 --> 38:31.751
Oh, no.

38:32.760 --> 38:33.636
Ow!

38:37.000 --> 38:39.468
- (ringing tone)
- Hello?

38:39.560 --> 38:43.678
Hey, Roger? How you doin'?
It's Mike Donnelly. Is Al there?

38:43.760 --> 38:46.320
Uh, gee, Mike.
Al's kind of busy right now.

38:46.400 --> 38:52.794
Ha, I know. I just wanted to tell him
I'm working my tail off for him up here,

38:52.880 --> 38:55.713
and there's no way
Al's gonna lose Gaffield County.

38:55.800 --> 38:59.031
That's great. I'll be sure to tell him.
Thanks for ringing up.

38:59.440 --> 39:02.557
Come on, let me talk to Al.
It's only gonna take a minute.

39:03.400 --> 39:05.960
Al doesn't wanna speak to you.

39:06.040 --> 39:09.157
What do you mean,
Al doesn't wanna speak to me? Why?

39:09.400 --> 39:11.391
Listen very carefully to me, Mike.

39:11.480 --> 39:14.358
You know what Al calls you
when you're not around here?

39:14.760 --> 39:18.275
The idiot. OK? All right?
Is that blunt enough for you?

39:18.360 --> 39:20.555
You are not going to speak to him now.

39:20.640 --> 39:25.077
And if I had my way, you wouldn't speak
to him after he's elected governor!

39:25.160 --> 39:27.151
(hangs up)

39:35.200 --> 39:38.397
Kovary. Man, that guy's a dick.

39:38.480 --> 39:41.790
Who is he to say
I can't talk to my own brother?

39:41.880 --> 39:43.598
You know?

39:43.680 --> 39:46.831
I ought to go down there
and straighten this thing out.

39:46.920 --> 39:48.911
What do you think, Steve?

39:49.240 --> 39:53.119
Al's speaking at that
Rock The Vote concert in Seattle.

39:53.680 --> 39:55.477
Steve?

39:58.560 --> 40:00.790
What do you think if I went down to...

40:15.920 --> 40:18.309
Oh, that's sad.

40:46.920 --> 40:48.911
(# rock music playing)

40:59.840 --> 41:01.432
Hey, it's cool. I was in.

41:02.360 --> 41:04.157
Where's the fire?

41:04.240 --> 41:07.630
Dude, we pay these bands' salaries
by buying a ticket to this shit.

41:07.720 --> 41:09.711
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

41:10.080 --> 41:12.548
Okey-dokey. Come on.

41:12.640 --> 41:16.918
Son, step away from this vector and
get into a different coordinate, pronto.

41:17.000 --> 41:19.798
There's no access for you
in this quadrant.

41:19.880 --> 41:23.429
Man, why don't you goose-step on
down to the women and children there

41:23.520 --> 41:27.195
and give them your power trip?
They might be impressed by it, asshole!

41:27.280 --> 41:29.999
- Yeah!
- Young fellow, I'll twist off your head

41:30.080 --> 41:33.834
and spike it onto the floors
of a nightmare you can't even imagine!

41:33.920 --> 41:37.117
I will dance with you
inside of the six-sided ring of fire,

41:37.200 --> 41:41.398
unless you move from this area
far and fast! Now!

41:41.480 --> 41:43.630
(music stops)

41:43.720 --> 41:45.517
Wow!

41:47.000 --> 41:50.151
Man, I liked that move.

41:50.600 --> 41:54.479
Yeah, I learnt it in the '84 Bounce-Off
over at Laguna Beach.

41:54.560 --> 41:58.519
- The one Mr T hosted.
- As a matter of fact it is. The same one.

42:07.800 --> 42:09.233
(chuckles nervously)

42:09.320 --> 42:11.276
Wow!

42:11.360 --> 42:13.396
Whoopsie-daisy.

42:14.160 --> 42:18.312
I was looking for my brother, Al
Donnelly. He's around here somewhere.

42:19.320 --> 42:23.108
So you fellas are... performers or...

42:26.040 --> 42:28.918
Oh, no, thanks. I never touch the stuff.

42:30.080 --> 42:33.436
There's enough in the air here
to get everybody high.

42:33.520 --> 42:37.752
Besides, it gives you the munchies.
God knows, I don't need that. Hey!

42:41.040 --> 42:43.429
But, uh...

42:43.520 --> 42:46.796
(emcee) Rock The Vote
presents Mudhoney.

43:03.680 --> 43:07.195
I don't think these kids wanna hear me
talk about bond issues, man.

43:07.280 --> 43:08.872
Al, we are lucky to be here.

43:08.960 --> 43:13.715
Just go out, tell the kids to vote,
do an interview with some MTV person

43:13.800 --> 43:15.756
and we're outta here.

43:15.840 --> 43:17.159
All right.

43:32.680 --> 43:36.639
# Like stacks and stacks of rats on rafts

43:36.720 --> 43:39.473
# Clutchin' anything we can

43:39.560 --> 43:42.677
# Stacks and stacks of rats on rafts

43:42.760 --> 43:45.911
# Weight of the world
crushin' our backs

43:46.320 --> 43:48.356
# Tooth for a tooth

43:49.440 --> 43:51.829
# Eye for an eye

43:52.880 --> 43:54.871
# You know it's the truth

43:55.880 --> 43:59.270
# And this is why

43:59.880 --> 44:03.953
So he says "Rectum?
